\begin_layout Standard
There are two important assumptions in the model.
 First, for simplicity, we assume that every category is dominated by assets
 or by nondurable consumption.
 Assets in this sense are always more expensive than the higher quality
 non-durable consumption.
 This gets around the issue that we effectively ignore the quality differences
